Constructor Detail

datasetFox

public datasetFox(java.net.URI serverURI,
                  java.lang.String id)
Deprecated. 
Once a datasetFox object is created, it is examined whether the server is alive and the dataset is valid. Otherwise an exception is thrown.

Parameters:
serverURI - the URL of the server including the port. The base URL of the server, e.g. "http://ambit.uni-plovdiv.bg:8080/ambit2"
id - the id of the dataset

run

public void run()
Deprecated. 
Constructs the Instances object. The dataset id and the server base URI must have been specified in the constructor of the dataset object. Example of use:

URI uri = new URI("http://ambit.uni-plovdiv.bg:8080/ambit2");
dataseFox dsf = new datasetFox(url,"8");
dsf.start();
Instances myData = dsf.getInstances();

Note: The url should not end with a /
